        <h3>Key Strategies Against Deepfakes</h3>
        <p>Several approaches are being developed to detect and prevent harmful deepfakes:</p>
        
        <div class="info-box">
            <h3>Industry Approaches to Combating Deepfakes</h3>
            <ol>
                <li><strong>Building a Safe Environment:</strong> Implementing safety measures, constant monitoring, and quick action against misuse</li>
                <li><strong>Content Credentials:</strong> Adding special marks or digital watermarks to AI-created content</li>
                <li><strong>Platform Safety:</strong> Spotting and removing harmful content from online platforms</li>
                <li><strong>Collaborative Efforts:</strong> Tech companies, non-profits, and governments working together</li>
                <li><strong>Regulatory Updates:</strong> Developing new laws and initiatives to protect people</li>
                <li><strong>Public Education:</strong> Helping people identify authentic versus fake content</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
        
        <h3>Detection Technologies</h3>
        <p>While deepfakes pose ethical and security concerns, AI technology is also making strides in detection:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>AI-Powered Detection:</strong> Machine learning models trained to identify visual artifacts</li>
            <li><strong>Digital Watermarking:</strong> Embedding invisible markers in authentic content</li>
            <li><strong>Blockchain Verification:</strong> Creating immutable records of original content</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p>As detection technology improves, it's becoming easier to identify deepfakes. However, the technology behind creating deepfakes is also advancing rapidly, making it an ongoing challenge.</p>
