        <div class="key-concept">
            <h3>Understanding Copyright</h3>
            <p>Copyright is a legal concept that grants creators and authors of original work exclusive rights to its use and distribution, ensuring they receive recognition and financial benefit from their creations. But what happens when the creator is an AI service or tool?</p>
        </div>
        
        <h3>Key Copyright Questions in AI</h3>
        <p>AI-generated content raises several important copyright questions:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Ownership:</strong> Who owns AI-generated content‚Äîthe user, the AI developer, or no one?</li>
            <li><strong>Training Data:</strong> How should copyright apply to data used to train AI models?</li>
            <li><strong>Derivative Works:</strong> Are AI-generated works based on existing content considered derivatives?</li>
            <li><strong>Creativity Standard:</strong> Does AI-generated work meet the creativity requirements for copyright?</li>
        </ul>
        
