        <h3>Content Credentials</h3>
        <p>To further build trust in AI-generated content, Microsoft has developed content credentials. This feature uses cryptographic methods to add an invisible digital watermark to all AI-generated images in Bing, including the time and date it was originally created.</p>
        
        <div class="info-box">
            <h3>Benefits of Content Credentials</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Provenance:</strong> Helps determine where content comes from</li>
                <li><strong>Authentication:</strong> Provides a way to verify content authenticity</li>
                <li><strong>Transparency:</strong> Gives creators and users better tools to decide what to trust</li>
                <li><strong>Protection:</strong> Safeguards against unauthorized use or manipulation</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
        <h3>Staying Informed and Vigilant</h3>
        <p>As consumers of digital content, we all have a responsibility to approach what we see online with a critical eye. Remember:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Question Sources:</strong> Consider where content is coming from and its credibility</li>
            <li><strong>Look for Verification:</strong> Check if content has been verified or contains digital credentials</li>
            <li><strong>Be Skeptical:</strong> Not everything you see or hear may be the truth</li>
            <li><strong>Report Suspicious Content:</strong> Help platforms identify potential deepfakes</li>
        </ul>
        
